edu.uidaho.junicon.runtime.junicon.operators

Class IconFunctions

  • java.lang.Object
    • edu.uidaho.junicon.runtime.junicon.operators.IconFunctions

  • public class IconFunctions
extends Object
    Defines the built-in Icon functions. The built-in functions are exposed as method references so they can be assignable.

    Normally, method references within a generated Junicon class are not intended to be assignable and will be ambiguous under Groovy if done so, since in Groovy a method takes precedence over a field closure with the same name in invocation, while in Java they are in separate namespaces. Assignment works here because we are exposing the references outside of their class.

    Provides support to memorize the association of a function name to its initial method reference, for use by proc("name",0).

    Memorization is one way to provide metadata for operators, functions, and keywords. Annotations are another way to provide metadata, using @MFunction, @Moperator, and @MKeyword.

    USAGE: When compiling to Java: import static IconFunctions.*;

      • ishift

        public static Object ishift(Object... args)
        Bit shift x by y positions. If y > 0, shifts left with zero fill. If y < 0, shifts right with sign extension. Vacated bit positions are filled with 0. For BigInteger, since << and >> do not work, must use shiftLeft() and shiftRight(). Error if either operand is not an integer.

      • move

        public static Object move(Object... args)
        Produces substring at &pos of length len. Increments &pos by len. Reverses the assignment to &pos if it is resumed. USAGE: move(len)

        &subject[&pos:&pos+len], or fail if len is out of range.

      • tab

        public static Object tab(Object... args)
        Produces substring from &pos to "to", exclusive. Sets &pos to "to". Reverses the assignment to &pos if it is resumed. USAGE: tab(to)
        Returns:
        &subject[&pos:to], or fail if "to" is out of range.

      • upto

        public static Object upto(Object... args)
        Generates locations where any character in c occurs in subj[from:to]. Accepts c as either character set or string equivalent. USAGE: upto(c, subj=&subject, from=1 if subj else pos, to=0)
        Returns:
        Iterator over the occurrences of s, or fail if not found.

      • many

        public static Object many(Object... args)

        Returns:
